article.headline: Radford 86, VMI 83
article.story: jrkg RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Martell McDuffy scored seven of his 19 points in overtime to lead Radford to an 86-83 win over VMI on Saturday VMI led 64-56 with 5:24 left in regulation, but McDuffy's basket in the lane with 1:18 left tied the score at 69-69. VMI, the nation's top scoring team at 92 points per game, took its only lead in overtime, 72-71, on Christian Hunter's 3-pointer with 4:33 remaining. McDuffy's jumper with 2:39 left put Radford ahead to stay, 77-75. Kenny Thomas sealed the win by making four free throws in the final 15 seconds. Joey Lynch-Flohr had 17 points and 12 rebounds while Amir Johnson scored 17 for Radford (10-17, 5-7 Big South). Thomas finished with 13 points. Reggie Williams had 31 points and 14 rebounds for VMI (13-13, 5-7). Chavis Holmes scored 22 and Hunter had 15 points.
